{
  "message": "fix: compute bound text height from actual content instead of hardcoded 20px\n\nMulti-line labels (especially with icons) overflowed their boxes because\nthe text element height was always 20px regardless of line count. The\ncentering formula (boxHeight - 20) / 2 pushed text too low, causing it\nto render outside the container.\n\nTwo fixes:\n- Bound text height now uses measureText() to get actual content height\n- Box height enforces a minimum based on text content + padding, even\n  when the user sets an explicit height smaller than the text needs",
